        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Remove</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Place a jack under vehicle frame and raise sufficiently to relieve weight from leaf
                    spring assemblies. Remove wheels. Refer to GROUP 17 - WHEELS in the CTS- 5000 Master Service Manual.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Tag alignment shims found at torque rod end mountings so they may be installed at the
                    same location upon reassembly.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove U-bolt nuts, U-bolts and top U-bolt seat.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove spring retaining pins from spring brackets and equalizer bracket. Remove leaf
                    spring assembly. Tag spacers found beneath or above leaf spring assembly so they may be installed at
                    the same location upon reassembly.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove equalizer pivot bolt, nut and lockwasher from equalizer bracket (
                    <hotlnk document="s03008_7.xml" xrefid="f0300806">Figure 6</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove adapter retainer and retainer bolt, if applicable. Tap outward on backside of
                    equalizer to produce clearance between equalizer and adapter. Remove equalizer from bracket.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
